# __NAME__

A VGI worker scaffolded with `make new-worker`. It registers one scalar
function, `__NAME___greet`, so you can validate the end-to-end pipeline
before adding more.

## Build and try it

```bash
go mod tidy
go build -o __NAME__ .
```

Then in DuckDB:

```sql
LOAD vgi;
ATTACH '__NAME__:./__NAME__' AS __NAME__;
SELECT __NAME__.__NAME___greet('world');
-- => 'hello, world!'
```

## Add a function

Each function needs: an args struct (with `vgi:"..."` tags), `Name()`,
`Metadata()`, `OnBindTyped`, and `ProcessTyped`. Wrap it with
`vgi.AsScalarFunction[args](&Impl{})` and pass to `w.RegisterScalar`.

For table-shaped functions see `vgi.TypedTableFunc` + `vgi.AsTableFunction`
in the upstream examples at
<https://github.com/Query-farm/vgi-go/tree/main/examples>.

## Logging

The scaffold wires `vgi.RegisterLoggingFlags`, so you can pass
`--log-level=debug`, `--log-format=json`, `--log-logger=vgi.rpc`, or set
`VGI_WORKER_DEBUG=1`.
